\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2530513\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 23, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104oaw1665702737082.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/oaw1665702737082.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/oaw1665702737082.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"oaw1665702737082\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Implement Referential Integrity in the Database\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">For some database systems, you can have the DBMS (instead of Uniface) manage referential integrity. To do so you need to execute the scripts created by the Create Script facility of the IDE in the target database.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"oaw1665702737082__context_w2699ab1b5b1_w2700ab1b5_w2701ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"oaw1665702737082__p_d47192e1_d47193e1_d47194e1\">To run the scripts:</p>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"oaw1665702737082__li_d23501e1_d23502e1_d23503e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Edit the scripts to specify the target database name.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"oaw1665702737082__li_d23504e1_d23505e1_d23506e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Execute the <code class=\"ph codeph\">validate RI</code> scripts.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"oaw1665702737082__li_d23507e1_d23508e1_d23509e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Investigate and resolve any reported violations of referential integrity.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"oaw1665702737082__li_d23510e1_d23511e1_d23512e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Execute the <code class=\"ph codeph\">create RI</code> scripts to enforce referential integrity.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"oaw1665702737082__li_d23513e1_d23514e1_d23515e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"oaw1665702737082__p_d47195e1_d47196e1_d47197e1\">Edit the application assignment file to configure the connector for database referential integrity support.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"oaw1665702737082__p_d47198e1_d47199e1_d47200e1\">DBMS connectors that support referential integrity in the database use a connector option to disable or enable Uniface referential integrity. The name of this option is DBMS-specific and the default state depends on the DBMS connector used. See the relevant documentation for the options available for your DBMS connector.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"oaw1665702737082__p_d47201e1_d47202e1_d47203e1\">For example, for a Microsoft SQL database, add\n                  MSS settings to the assignment file, including the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">dbms ri</span>\n                  option to disable Uniface referential integrity.</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[DRIVER_SETTINGS]\nMSS U5.2\nUSYS$MSS_PARAMS identifiers = quoted, procedures=on, dbms ri</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"oaw1665702737082__p_d47204e1_d47205e1_d47206e1\">See the relevant connector documentation for your DBMS connector.</p>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wly1665702737011.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Generate Referential Integrity Scripts</a><p>For some database systems, you can have the DBMS (instead of Uniface) manage referential integrity. To do so you need to generate referential integrity scripts and have the database administrator execute those scripts in the target database.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dln1665702622802.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Create Script Facility</a></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hvg1704363446431.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Ensuring Referential Integrity</a><p>You can ensure the referential integrity of data in Uniface applications by defining constraints in object properties, ProcScript, and database scripts.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lsp1665702531534.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Database Connectors</a><p>To access, retrieve, and store data, Uniface provides database connectors that translate Uniface I/O requests into the target database's data definition and manipulation languages.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530513\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530513\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Implement Referential Integrity in the Database Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 23, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Implement Referential Integrity in the Database For some database systems, you can have the DBMS (instead of Uniface) manage referential integrity. To do so you need to execute the scripts created by the Create Script facility of the IDE in the target database. To run the scripts: Edit the scripts to specify the target database name. Execute the validate RI scripts. Investigate and resolve any reported violations of referential integrity. Execute the create RI scripts to enforce referential integrity. Edit the application assignment file to configure the connector for database referential integrity support. DBMS connectors that support referential integrity in the database use a connector option to disable or enable Uniface referential integrity. The name of this option is DBMS-specific and the default state depends on the DBMS connector used. See the relevant documentation for the options available for your DBMS connector. For example, for a Microsoft SQL database, add MSS settings to the assignment file, including the dbms ri option to disable Uniface referential integrity. [DRIVER_SETTINGS] MSS U5.2 USYS$MSS_PARAMS identifiers = quoted, procedures=on, dbms ri Copy See the relevant connector documentation for your DBMS connector. Related Links Generate Referential Integrity Scripts For some database systems, you can have the DBMS (instead of Uniface) manage referential integrity. To do so you need to generate referential integrity scripts and have the database administrator execute those scripts in the target database. Create Script Facility Ensuring Referential Integrity You can ensure the referential integrity of data in Uniface applications by defining constraints in object properties, ProcScript, and database scripts. Database Connectors To access, retrieve, and store data, Uniface provides database connectors that translate Uniface I/O requests into the target database's data definition and manipulation languages. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}